[
    {
        "text": "Hi, I’m Francis, ",
        "start": 5.781,
        "duration": 1.382
    },
    {
        "text": "the host of this show \"Cooking with Dog.\"",
        "start": 7.163,
        "duration": 2.772
    },
    {
        "text": "First, let’s make the marinade.",
        "start": 18.569,
        "duration": 2.706
    },
    {
        "text": "In a small pot, combine the sake ",
        "start": 21.275,
        "duration": 2.973
    },
    {
        "text": "and the mirin.  ",
        "start": 25.279,
        "duration": 1.482
    },
    {
        "text": "Turn on the burner.",
        "start": 28.067,
        "duration": 1.816
    },
    {
        "text": "Bring it to a boil and let the alcohol evaporate ",
        "start": 31.236,
        "duration": 3.151
    },
    {
        "text": "until you can’t smell it anymore.",
        "start": 34.387,
        "duration": 2.834
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, it is ready.",
        "start": 39.873,
        "duration": 2.018
    },
    {
        "text": "Pour the mixture onto a plate.",
        "start": 43.91,
        "duration": 2.531
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, add the vinegar, ",
        "start": 48.844,
        "duration": 1.983
    },
    {
        "text": "yuzu citrus juice, ",
        "start": 53.018,
        "duration": 1.718
    },
    {
        "text": "dashi kombu seaweed, ",
        "start": 55.534,
        "duration": 1.507
    },
    {
        "text": "dried red chili pepper ",
        "start": 57.041,
        "duration": 2.195
    },
    {
        "text": "and soy sauce.",
        "start": 60.954,
        "duration": 1.468
    },
    {
        "text": "Stir to mix.  ",
        "start": 63.185,
        "duration": 1.669
    },
    {
        "text": "You can use any type of sour citrus juice ",
        "start": 64.929,
        "duration": 3.016
    },
    {
        "text": "instead of the yuzu juice.",
        "start": 67.945,
        "duration": 2.185
    },
    {
        "text": "Next, make numerous cuts ",
        "start": 72.956,
        "duration": 1.829
    },
    {
        "text": "along the long green onion diagonally.",
        "start": 74.785,
        "duration": 2.957
    },
    {
        "text": "The small cuts will help it to absorb the flavor ",
        "start": 77.941,
        "duration": 3.167
    },
    {
        "text": "and also help soften the texture.",
        "start": 81.108,
        "duration": 2.735
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, cut the onion into 4cm (1.6”) pieces.",
        "start": 85.028,
        "duration": 4.384
    },
    {
        "text": "As for the bell pepper, cut it the same size as the onion.",
        "start": 90.448,
        "duration": 4.503
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, let’s make the Salmon Yakizuke.",
        "start": 96.858,
        "duration": 3.194
    },
    {
        "text": "Add the sake to the salmon.",
        "start": 100.552,
        "duration": 2.769
    },
    {
        "text": "And coat both sides evenly.",
        "start": 104.37,
        "duration": 2.767
    },
    {
        "text": "Next, add the vegetable oil to a pan.",
        "start": 111.058,
        "duration": 3.316
    },
    {
        "text": "Turn on the burner ",
        "start": 115.209,
        "duration": 1.934
    },
    {
        "text": "and add the long green onion and the bell pepper.",
        "start": 117.422,
        "duration": 3.889
    },
    {
        "text": "Stir-fry the vegetables.",
        "start": 123.802,
        "duration": 2.196
    },
    {
        "text": "You can also use asparagus, ",
        "start": 126.114,
        "duration": 2.135
    },
    {
        "text": "snap peas, onion or mushrooms instead.",
        "start": 128.249,
        "duration": 3.87
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, the vegetables are deliciously browned.",
        "start": 132.867,
        "duration": 3.669
    },
    {
        "text": "Place them into the marinade.",
        "start": 140.971,
        "duration": 2.636
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, with a paper towel, ",
        "start": 146.505,
        "duration": 2.103
    },
    {
        "text": "remove the moisture from the salmon.",
        "start": 148.608,
        "duration": 2.968
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, using a mesh strainer, ",
        "start": 153.774,
        "duration": 2.402
    },
    {
        "text": "sprinkle all purpose flour on both sides of the fish.",
        "start": 156.176,
        "duration": 3.95
    },
    {
        "text": "This will help to create a nicely browned surface ",
        "start": 160.491,
        "duration": 3.435
    },
    {
        "text": "and also absorb the marinade.",
        "start": 163.926,
        "duration": 2.567
    },
    {
        "text": "Add oil again ",
        "start": 169.497,
        "duration": 1.574
    },
    {
        "text": "and reheat the pan.  ",
        "start": 171.687,
        "duration": 2.087
    },
    {
        "text": "Place the salmon into the pan.",
        "start": 175.627,
        "duration": 3.062
    },
    {
        "text": "Saute the top side first ",
        "start": 179.305,
        "duration": 1.901
    },
    {
        "text": "so that you can present a beautifully browned surface.",
        "start": 181.206,
        "duration": 3.641
    },
    {
        "text": "Occasionally shake the pan to brown evenly.",
        "start": 185.676,
        "duration": 3.443
    },
    {
        "text": "Cover and saute on low heat.",
        "start": 190.612,
        "duration": 2.868
    },
    {
        "text": "When the bottom is golden brown, flip it over.",
        "start": 198.876,
        "duration": 3.918
    },
    {
        "text": "Brown the other side.",
        "start": 203.295,
        "duration": 1.976
    },
    {
        "text": "You can also grill the salmon to give the skin a crisp texture, ",
        "start": 207.254,
        "duration": 4.514
    },
    {
        "text": "making the dish more delicious.",
        "start": 211.768,
        "duration": 2.382
    },
    {
        "text": "Mmmmm. This looks so good!",
        "start": 217.718,
        "duration": 3.035
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, it is ready.",
        "start": 222.323,
        "duration": 2.421
    },
    {
        "text": "Place the salmon onto the plate.",
        "start": 225.828,
        "duration": 2.609
    },
    {
        "text": "Spoon the marinade over the ingredients ",
        "start": 230.156,
        "duration": 2.75
    },
    {
        "text": "and let them sit until cool.",
        "start": 232.906,
        "duration": 2.572
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, the Yakizuke has absorbed the flavor.",
        "start": 236.975,
        "duration": 3.587
    },
    {
        "text": "Place the kombu seaweed ",
        "start": 240.678,
        "duration": 1.558
    },
    {
        "text": "and a piece of long green onion onto a plate.",
        "start": 242.236,
        "duration": 3.612
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, lean the salmon against them.",
        "start": 246.899,
        "duration": 3.623
    },
    {
        "text": "Garnish with the bell pepper and the long green onion.",
        "start": 252.571,
        "duration": 3.88
    },
    {
        "text": "Finally, spoon the marinade over the salmon.",
        "start": 257.622,
        "duration": 3.631
    },
    {
        "text": "This is a local dish in Niigata Prefecture ",
        "start": 266.055,
        "duration": 3.17
    },
    {
        "text": "and it was originally made at home ",
        "start": 269.225,
        "duration": 2.132
    },
    {
        "text": "to preserve fresh salmon which are caught in that area.",
        "start": 271.357,
        "duration": 4.442
    },
    {
        "text": "You can enjoy the dish immediately ",
        "start": 285.581,
        "duration": 2.4
    },
    {
        "text": "or keep it in the fridge for several hours ",
        "start": 287.981,
        "duration": 2.92
    },
    {
        "text": "to help it absorb more delicious flavor.",
        "start": 290.901,
        "duration": 3.468
    },
    {
        "text": "Good luck in the kitchen!",
        "start": 294.369,
        "duration": 1.541
    }
]